data.title: His Royal Highness Prince El Hassan bin Talal and Minister of the Polish government Pawe≈Ç Soloch attended a dinner to commemorate the 25th anniversary of establishing the Visegrad Group
data.meta_description: On March 16, 2016 The Czech Ambassador, Petr Hladik, held an official dinner to commemorate the 25th anniversary of founding the Visegrad
data.text:
H.R.H. Prince El Hassan mentioned his close personal relationship with the founders of the Visegrad Group and emphasised on how important and inspiring the successful cooperation among the Visegrad countries is for the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan and its neighbouring countries. Minister Soloch concentrated on security aspects of the cooperation of the Visegrad countries and praised the role of the Czech Embassy in Amman as NATO Contact Point Embassy to Jordan.

H.R.H. Prince El Hasan called for closer cooperation and greater involvement of the Visegrad Group regarding the ongoing armed conflict in the region and help that Jordan needs to overcome this crisis.
